---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Parques Nacionales puerto varas | Guias completas" description="Guias completas de parques nacionales en puerto varas. Informacion actualizada con tips locales.">
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6D28D9 0%, #DB2777 100%);">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 lg:py-20">
      <span class="text-5xl mb-4 block">🌲</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-4">Parques Nacionales</h1>
      <p class="text-white/80 text-lg max-w-2xl">Todo lo que necesitas saber antes de ir.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6" set:html={`<a href="/parques/parque-nacional-vicente-perez-rosales" class="group block bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden no-underline hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300"><div class="h-48 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-pink-50 flex items-center justify-center relative"><span class="text-5xl">🌲</span><span class="absolute top-3 right-3 bg-white/90 text-xs font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Variable según sendero</span></div><div class="p-6"><h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 group-hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors mb-2">El Corazón de la Patagonia Andina</h2><p class="text-gray-500 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">Cascadas, volcanes y bosques nativos en el parque más antiguo de Chile</p><div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2"><span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">⏱️ Día completo recomendado</span><span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">📍 60 km (1.5 horas en auto)</span><span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">🗓️ Octubre a abril</span></div></div></a>
      <a href="/parques/parque-nacional-alkofal-puerto-varas" class="group block bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden no-underline hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300"><div class="h-48 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-pink-50 flex items-center justify-center relative"><span class="text-5xl">🌲</span><span class="absolute top-3 right-3 bg-white/90 text-xs font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Fácil a moderada</span></div><div class="p-6"><h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 group-hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors mb-2">El Último Pulmón Verde de Puerto Varas</h2><p class="text-gray-500 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">Bosque costero y senderos junto al mar en el sur de Chile</p><div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2"><span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">⏱️ 3 a 6 horas</span><span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">📍 8 km (15 minutos)</span><span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">🗓️ Todo el año</span></div></div></a>
      <a href="/parques/reserva-nacional-lobos-marinos-puerto-varas" class="group block bg-white border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden no-underline hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300"><div class="h-48 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-pink-50 flex items-center justify-center relative"><span class="text-5xl">🌲</span><span class="absolute top-3 right-3 bg-white/90 text-xs font-medium px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Fácil (tours en bote)</span></div><div class="p-6"><h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 group-hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors mb-2">Encuentro con los Gigantes del Mar</h2><p class="text-gray-500 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">Colonias de lobos marinos y aves marinas en la costa de Puerto Varas</p><div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2"><span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">⏱️ 4-5 horas ida y vuelta</span><span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">📍 120 km (2 horas en auto)</span><span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">🗓️ Noviembre a marzo</span></div></div></a>`}></div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>